Class TreeBag<E extends java.lang.Comparable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • TreeBag<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable

    public class TreeBag<E extends java.lang.Comparable>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable
    This class is a homework assignment; An TreeBag is a collection of int numbers.
    Limitations:
    Beyond Integer.MAX_VALUE elements, countOccurrences, and size are wrong.
    Note:
    This file contains only blank implementations ("stubs") because this is a Programming Project for my students.

      • retrieve

        public E retrieve(E target)
        Retrieve a specified element from this bag.
        Parameters:
        target - the element to locate in the bag
        Returns:
        the return value is a reference to the found element in the tree
        Postcondition:
        If target was found in the bag, then method returns a reference to a comparable element. If the target was not found then the method returns null. The bag remains unchanged.

      • remove

        public boolean remove(E target)
        Remove one copy of a specified element from this bag.
        Parameters:
        target - the element to remove from the bag
        Postcondition:
        If target was found in the bag, then one copy of target has been removed and the method returns true. Otherwise the bag remains unchanged and the method returns false.

      • toString

        public void toString(BTNode<E> node,
                     java.lang.StringBuilder out)
        Recursively traverses the tree in-order as specified by the generic element's compareTo method. Builds a string containing the in-order output of every element using the passed-in StringBuilder object. This method does not return anything; instead, the StringBuilder object will contain the final output.
        Postcondition:
        Outputs all elements in the tree to Screen. Does not change the structure
